message.content: The paper most likely belongs to the "cs.CV" (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category, as it deals with visual question answering. Other possible sub-categories could include "cs.CL" (Computation and Language) due to the natural language processing aspect of the method, "cs.AI" (Artificial Intelligence) due to the use of neural networks, "cs.LG" (Machine Learning) for the same reason, and "cs.IR" (Information Retrieval) due to the use of a knowledge base to extract information.
